Both pre-election and post-election violence are instigated by political kingpins.Those extra seats are supposedly meant to appease these warlords, lest they incite citizens to violence. It is not in doubt that the extra political seats proposed in the Building Bridges Initiative will burden an already overtaxed citizenry. We need anything but a bloated government.
But a little memory jog will help. It is argued that the proposed top positions won’t cure divisive politics. Whereas this sounds reasonably true, a ground check reveals conflicting realities.



