Whereas they mill campaign rallies, most of them vanish during polling day. Politicians know this; the more reason they ignore them.
Ask yourself why politicians tell blatant lies during campaigns. They are well aware that their voters are mainly elderly villagers, who can’t make head from tail of their stories!
Idle youth will at best be engaged as tent erectors, hecklers and missile launchers, while those in the middle class indifferently watch the unfolding events on their super plasma screens.
A recent example is when university students attempted a protest upon getting wind of the government’s intention to increase their fees. But they have remained silent whenever injustices are happen. Youth cannot afford to be by-standers. 
If they detest BBI, for instance, they have over 10 million votes with them. But they are equally beholden to tribalism and ignorance; ingredients antithetical to rational decisions.
I’m becoming convinced that Kenyans often get what they deserve. The country has a shortage of fools indeed. Sonko will need 24 elected senators to survive his removal from office. The DP's ally, Feisal Bader, garnered 15,251 votes to trounce ODM’s Omar Boga who secured 10,444 votes in the hotly contested poll. Ministry of Health estimates that the first batch of the recipients will cover 20 per cent of the country’s population.